{"id": "EUVD-2025-31205", "enisaUuid": "d207fa28-8799-360e-afc6-46160344f220", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nio_uring/futex: ensure io_futex_wait() cleans up properly on failure\n\nThe io_futex_data is allocated upfront and assigned to the io_kiocb\nasync_data field, but the request isn't marked with REQ_F_ASYNC_DATA\nat that point. Those two should always go together, as the flag tells\nio_uring whether the field is valid or not.\n\nAdditionally, on failure cleanup, the futex handler frees the data but\ndoes not clear ->async_data. Clear the data and the flag in the error\npath as well.\n\nThanks to Trend Micro Zero Day Initiative and particularly ReDress for\nreporting this.", "datePublished": "2025-09-05T18:31:27", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-17T15:30:57", "baseScore": 8.8, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:C/C:H/I:H/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/d9f93172820a53ab42c4b0e5e65291f4f9d00ad2", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/d34c04152df517c59979b4bf2a47f491e06d3256", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/508c1314b342b78591f51c4b5dadee31a88335df", "https://www.zerodayinitiative.com/advisories/ZDI-25-915/", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-39698"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-39698"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.0, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "003c7bb9-44c8-3c35-8904-9b9ecd858fa6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.16.4"}, {"id": "0c951e9f-1f42-33f1-b1f5-2bc3cd808bb9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "194bb58c6090e39bd7d9b9c888a079213628e1f6 <d9f93172820a53ab42c4b0e5e65291f4f9d00ad2"}, {"id": "2ef69d1a-03cb-3c66-a6cb-2482f2e56523", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.44"}, {"id": "34a87db2-8fb8-3fd1-95a1-ba4b4cad1c1e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "194bb58c6090e39bd7d9b9c888a079213628e1f6 <d34c04152df517c59979b4bf2a47f491e06d3256"}, {"id": "434a41fe-4457-34bb-a8c5